title: [SOLVED]820-3476 2014 Turning on by battery not by AC
message:
Liquid Damage Macbook Pro

Originally No green light no power... dead

U3210 was short. removed it and replaced it 

U7090 had broken trace. replaced and jumped wire

U7100 had broken trace too. jumped wire and replaced

Now i get green light but doesnt turn on. plug in with battery and it turns on. However does not charge battery

so i replaced u7100 maybe a bad one. same thing.

Please let me know what other steps i can take

TIA

title: [SOLVED]820-3476 2014 Turning on by battery not by AC
message:
What voltage is on PPBUS_G3H with charger only?
Measure resistance between pins 17/18 and 27/28 at U7100.
Check traces and resistors for corrosion in that area...

title: [SOLVED]820-3476 2014 Turning on by battery not by AC
message:
PPBUS_G3H with charger only -3.73v (that's low?

17/18 4ohm

and 27/28 20ohm (this seems low)

title: [SOLVED]820-3476 2014 Turning on by battery not by AC
message: PPBIS_G3H should be 12.56V, remove F7140 and check if PPBUS_G3H goes high.......
